cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and deep learning techniques for facial expression recognition, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new 3D convolutional neural network architecture, which falls under the purview of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The LBV layer proposed in the paper is designed to reduce the number of trainable parameters, which could also be relevant to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed model on different datasets, which could be relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning techniques for facial expression recognition suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
